Data: Starc to Roy, no run nice line and length in the channel outside off, lets it go

Starc to Roy, no run trapped in front but Roy reviews. That was a mighty close shout, pitched in line and nipped back in. Height may be an issue. and it is going over the stumps, so Roy survives. But he was playing all around that one, beaten by the movement inwards and groping with bat well away from ball
Starc to Roy, 2 runs pacy inswinger at 88mph, almost yorker length on off, Roy is coming forward but gets an inside edge that rolls to fine leg
Starc to Roy, no run going across him from over the wicket and tailing into him. Roy goes to drive it, but inside edges onto pad
Starc to Roy, no run excellent line, hitting the hard length and nibbling at off, defended from the crease. Nips into him a tad again
Starc to Roy, no run length going a mite across him, stays beside it and pushes to point
Hazlewood to Bairstow, no run drops short of midwicket Back of a length outside off, he goes to pull, gets a top edge that dinks down just out of reach of the fielder
Hazlewood to Bairstow, no run good length on the stumps, patted back
Hazlewood to Bairstow, no run Good length on off, defended from the crease
Hazlewood to Bairstow, no run Back of a length wide of off, flays at it with feet rooted, no connection
Hazlewood to Bairstow, no run short outside off, Bairstow looks to free his arms with the pull but can't lay bat on it
Hazlewood to Bairstow, no run length outside off, nudged into the covers but straight to the fielder to complete a maiden over

Starc to Roy, FOUR runs length ball pushed across him, pushed sweetly but straight to wide-ish mid-on... and straight through him! Races away for four. Sloppy stuff from Cummins, and Starc looks to the sky in frustration
Starc to Roy, no run length ball at 88mph/142kph outside the off stump. Roy has a flash but can't lay bat on it
Starc to Roy, no run good length, angling across the right-hander with a bit of width at 90mph/145kph. Roy throws the bat again, but again can't make contact
Starc to Roy, 1 wide short ball at the left shoulder, 90mph/146kph, but too straight and too high
Starc to Roy, no run slightly full of a length, Roy skips outside leg stump to give himself room to hit over the off-side ring, but misses it completely
Starc to Roy, no run short ball in at the biceps, down the leg side, but not called wide this time as Roy ducks

Starc to Roy, 1 run slightly full of a length on sixth stump, Roy shuffles across to the off side and plays tip-and-run to mid-on, just about making his ground as Cummins throws slightly wide of the stumps
Hazlewood to Roy, no run banged in on a length at 85mph/137kph, Roy is beaten for pace and struck on the back thigh. Bit of seam movement into the batsman
Hazlewood to Roy, FOUR runs uses his feet to skip down and give himself room to flay through wide mid-off for four! No timing, right off the toe, but enough power to get through the ring
Hazlewood to Roy, no run hard length on off stump, chokes the bat with the bottom hand to work to short midwicket
Hazlewood to Roy, no run length on sixth stump, nudged to short extra cover
Hazlewood to Roy, FOUR runs just a fraction overpitched for once, and Roy clips off the pads through square leg for four

Hazlewood to Roy, FOUR runs shorter this time but too wide, and Roy flays through point for four more! He's up and running now, square-cutting to get it in between backward point and cover in the circle

Starc to Bairstow, OUT edged, gone! 90mph/145kph, pushed across the right-hander, and Bairstow nicks off. Starc had been hooping the ball into the batsmen but this one held its line and took the edge of Bairstow's apologetic prod. Australia get their breakthrough
Starc to Root, no run back of a length outside off, Root drops the hands and sways inside the line
Starc to Root, no run slightly full of a length on fourth stump, driven to mid-off
Starc to Root, no run banged in on a length, Root opens the face to guide it into the covers
Starc to Root, 4 leg byes nibbles in from back of a length, and Root looks to flick into the leg side. It strikes him on the backside, and runs away fine for four leg byes

Starc to Root, no run inside-edged into the body, and Root hits the deck! Length ball pushed across him as he looked to drive through the covers, but he only managed to inside-edge into the back knee and will get some treatment from the physio
Hazlewood to Roy, 1 run bit of nibble away, but Root steers behind square on the leg side as he comes across
Hazlewood to Root, 1 run shimmies down to flick into the leg side and scamper through for a single to wide mid-on. Doesn't look like that injury is causing him too much trouble, then
Hazlewood to Roy, 1 run length outside off, Roy swivel-pulls into the leg side but hits the sweeper
Hazlewood to Root, 1 run full and straight, nudged in front of square on the leg side via the inside half of the bat
Hazlewood to Roy, no run short outside off, Roy uses his feet to come down but can only swat to the cover-point fielder
Hazlewood to Roy, no run length in the channel, dabbed into the ground on the crease
Starc to Root, 1 wide sprayed very wide of the off stump. Left alone, and called wide
Starc to Root, no run beauty! Straight past the outside edge as Root is half-forward, half-back while defending. Starc angles this across him, and a hint of nibble away takes it past the bat
Starc to Root, no run wild waft outside the off stump at a 90mph/146kph half-volley, and no connection
Starc to Root, no run banged in on a length, steered to point on the bounce with an open face
Starc to Root, no run hint of movement in off the seam as Root drives a full ball to mid-off. 91mph/146kph - good pace throughout this first spell from Starc
Starc to Root, no run length in the channel, Root attempts his trademark guide down to third man but is cramped for room, and can't get bat on it. Looks out of nick!

Starc to Root, OUT length on off stump, nudged into the covers for a sharp single and a direct hit means he's gone! Roy was running to the danger end and was miles short of his ground. Brilliant stuff from Stoinis, who picks up and throws in one smooth movement, and sets off in celebration after knocking down the stumps. Australia are buzzing!
Hazlewood to Root, no run length outside off, bit of width but it dies off the surface and flies under Root's bat
Hazlewood to Root, no run nips in off the seam to hit Root on the thigh pad. No appeal, going over the top and possibly down leg too
Hazlewood to Root, no run beauty! Nips away off the seam to beat Root's defensive push as he comes down the pitch. Wry smiles from both bowler and batsman
Hazlewood to Root, no run length on the hip, clipped into the leg side and Stoinis at short midwicket dives to his right at full stretch to cut it off
Hazlewood to Root, no run width outside off, Root frees his arms to cut and connects well, but can't beat Maxwell at backward point on the bounce
Hazlewood to Root, no run length on off stump, Root defends to short cover to complete a second maiden for Hazlewood
Starc to Morgan, no run length ball on fifth stump, beats Morgan's dangled bat. No real foot movement
Starc to Morgan, 1 run length on the pads, whipped down to long leg
Starc to Root, no run outswinger on a length, left alone
Starc to Root, no run banged in, back of a length at 88mph/142kph, and steered into the off side
Starc to Root, no run bit of width outside off, Root swings and misses again! Shaped for a wristy cut but lost his shape and was late on the shot
Starc to Root, no run back of a length, more width outside off, and Root bottom-edges the cut through to Carey on the bounce
Hazlewood to Root, no run slightly full of a length on fourth stump, nudged to short cover
Hazlewood to Root, 1 run length outside off, steered behind square on the off side to finally get off 2!
Hazlewood to Morgan, no run back of a length, nudged towards mid-off with a straight bat
Hazlewood to Morgan, no run fuller on leg stump, clipped to mid-on by Morgan
Hazlewood to Morgan, no run length ball outside off, Morgan has a flirt but can't lay bat on it
Cummins to Root, no run length on off stump, nudged to short midwicket
Cummins to Root, no run very full on off stump at 88mph/142kph, Root digs it out, straight to short midwicket on the bounce
Cummins to Root, no run nips in from a length, clipped to square leg
Cummins to Root, FOUR runs or maybe it was! Length ball on fourth stump, Root heaves across the line and gets it just past backward square leg in the ring
Cummins to Root, FOUR runs beautiful shot! Bit of a half-volley from Cummins, too much width and Root brings out an exquisite cover drive. It flies off the middle of that new bat and away for four!
Cummins to Root, 1 run length on off stump, Root rocks onto the back foot and clips through square leg to keep the strike
Hazlewood to Root, no run length in the channel, nudged to Maxwell at point
Hazlewood to Root, no run length outside off, checked drive out to mid-off
Hazlewood to Root, no run length on off stump, defended back to the bowler
Hazlewood to Root, no run length on fourth stump, Root defends to short cover on the bounce
Hazlewood to Root, no run slightly overpitched on fourth stump, Root drives down the ground with a straight bat but can't beat mid-on
Hazlewood to Root, 1 run length on fifth stump, steered down to third man to keep the strike
Cummins to Root, no run length on fifth stump at 88mph/141kph, nudged to short cover
Cummins to Root, no run length on sixth stump, Root gets across to work towards midwicket

Cummins to Root, no run beaten! Root's bat has lost its magical powers. Immaculate line and length from Cummins, Root is cramped for room while shaping to drive and it flies past the shoulder of the bat
Cummins to Root, no run length on fourth stump, stabbed to backward point with an open face
Cummins to Root, no run back of a length outside off, steered to backward point where Maxwell leaps like a salmon to his left and keeps the pressure building
Cummins to Root, no run slightly fuller on fourth stump, Root's hand comes off the bat as he shapes to drive and it dribbles towards cover
Marsh to Morgan, no run pushed across him, Morgan times this sweetly in front of square but can't get it past cover point, Sams on as a sub, in the ring
Marsh to Morgan, no run Marsh is tight to the stumps, and Morgan is cramped for room shaping to cut

Marsh to Morgan, no run back of a length ball, doesn't really get up off the surface and Marsh belts out an appeal as it hits Morgan on the pad! Finch isn't interested, though. Slower ball, and looked like it was going over the top
Marsh to Morgan, no run length ball nudged towards mid-on, tidy start from Marsh
Marsh to Morgan, no run pushed across Morgan, who tries to cut but is cramped for room, and bottom-edges through to Carey on the bounce
Marsh to Morgan, no run nagging line on off stump, Morgan defends from a length and that's another maiden
Cummins to Root, no run length outside off, jags back in and he bunts it towards mid-on
Cummins to Root, no run ooh, swing and a miss. Not full enough to drive and on the fifth stump, Root aimed an ambitious drive on the up but didn't connect
Cummins to Root, 1 run bangs this in short outside off but Root rides the bounce nicely to steer it to third man from his chest
Cummins to Morgan, no run length ball on leg, going across him, defended back down the pitch
Cummins to Morgan, 1 wide bouncer, but banged down too short over leg stump and that'll be a wide for height
Cummins to Morgan, no run follows it up with a better bouncer, over leg stump again but this one forces Morgan to duck under it
Cummins to Morgan, no run keeps up the short ball attack, this one into the rib cage and Morgan defends it back from the crease
Marsh to Root, no run fuller on off, almost falls over while going across and clipping towards mid-on

Marsh to Root, FOUR runs back of a length outside off, punched off the back foot and there's a misfield at point which means it goes through and finds the boundary. Marnus there I think, who was moving to his left and tumbled to stop it but made a hash of it
Marsh to Root, no run
Marsh to Root, no run back of a length on off, whipped off the back foot but can't go past midwicket
Marsh to Root, 1 run length ball, straighter, flicked to midwicket's right for a single

Marsh to Morgan, 2 runs another misfield, by short midwicket this time. Shimmies down the track and flicks it off his pads. The fielder lets it go through, though admittedly he didn't have a whole lot of time to react. Still should have stopped it. They get a couple
Cummins to Root, 3 runs uppish but in the gap through backward point. Full outside off, he opens the face to drive
Cummins to Morgan, no run length on the stumps, trying to deny him room. Morgan cuts from close to his body but point stops it to his right
Cummins to Morgan, no run fuller on the stumps, tries to stroke it through cover, but not timed
Cummins to Morgan, 1 run short ball, Morgan decides to attack but gets an under-edge on the pull that rolls down to fine leg
Cummins to Root, no run half an appeal as this one is dug in short and sliding down leg. He moves inside the line to pull, but doesn't connect.
Cummins to Root, no run jags back in sharply from outside off and Root wears a blow on the abdomen trying to pull this
Marsh to Morgan, 1 run fuller on the pads, turned to deep square leg
Marsh to Root, no run back of a length outside off, doesn't bounce much, Root stays beside it and punches to point
Marsh to Root, no run still not finding the gaps is Root. Back of a length on off, goes on the back foot to punch, straight to cover
Marsh to Root, no run half a step down and flicks it, beats midwicket but can't beat mid-on who was moving to his right to cut it off. Still no single for Root

Marsh to Root, no run and that is what happens when you're struggling for runs. Gets one a bit short and pulls fiercely. Not perfectly timed but would have got runs if he had placed it better. But short midwicket dives to his left and saves
Marsh to Root, 1 run finally gets one away. Length outside off, gets down low and late cuts to third man
Stoinis to Root, no run slower ball back of a length to start off, on leg stump. Root was moving to pull but too early into the shot and ends up missing it
Stoinis to Root, 1 run fuller outside off, flicked to mid-on by walking across and gets a single
Stoinis to Morgan, no run good length nipping across gently, defended solidly from the crease

Stoinis to Morgan, FOUR runs just out of reach of Cummins at deep square leg. Not sure Stoinis intended to bowl a short ball on leg stump given his field, but Morgan moves across and swivels to pull hard. Cummins at deep square leg dives to his left, would have been a spectacular catch if he had got to it. But it eludes him
Stoinis to Morgan, no run length on the stumps, nudged to midwicket
Stoinis to Morgan, 2 runs back of a length outside off, Morgan stays low and cuts it late to third man's left. They sprint back for the second
Marsh to Root, 1 leg bye fuller sliding down leg, misses the flick but it takes the pad to backward square leg and they get a single
Marsh to Morgan, no run down the track but this was dug into the pitch on a line just outside off, and Morgan can't get to the pitch, ends up bunting it with a flat bat to cover
Marsh to Morgan, 1 wide strays down leg a bit with this back of length one and he'll have to re-bowl that
Marsh to Morgan, 1 run sticking in the pitch a bit, on a length on the stumps, Morgan backing away but can't create enough room, ends up jabbing it close to his body to mid-off

Marsh to Root, 1 run some shape in the air and misfield by Warner at cover allows a single. Strange one. Full ball driven, but not timed, and Warner just seemed to lose it while bending down to collect
Marsh to Morgan, 1 run down the track again, gets a bit of an inside edge to deep square leg trying to swing through the line
Marsh to Root, no run clipped to midwicket
Stoinis to Morgan, 1 run back of a length on leg stump, swivels pulls it, gets a bit of an under-edge to fine leg
Stoinis to Root, 1 run back of a length on the fourth stump, he moves across and pulls to deep square leg. Ball didn't really bounce much
Stoinis to Morgan, 1 run nicely done, length ball going across him, waits and late cuts it to third man. There is a fielder there so only one run
Stoinis to Root, FOUR runs good shot and that will give Root a bit of a breather. Back of a length on off, stays still and punches through cover with beautiful timing. Finds the boundary
Stoinis to Root, no run length ball nipping in, jabbed towards backward point
Stoinis to Root, SIX runs bang goes Root! Dances down the track and disdainfully pulls a short ball. Nice thwacking sound off the bat as it flies hard and straight over midwicket.
Marsh to Morgan, no run length ball, cramping him for room, tries to cut from close to his body. Ball doesn't travel much towards short third man, no single

Marsh to Morgan, 3 runs down the track and goes over the in-field. Bat turned in his hand and not timed that at all but it lands safely over extra cover. Not enough legs on it to go to the boundary though
Marsh to Root, no run length on the stumps, goes back and across to flick, but can't beat midwicket
Marsh to Root, 1 run too full, tailing onto leg stump, flicked to fine leg off the toe-end of the bat
Marsh to Morgan, 1 run length ball down leg, flicked off his hips to deep backward square leg
Marsh to Root, no run length on off, dabbed towards point. No single as the fielder comes swooping in
Zampa to Morgan, 1 run tossed up on the stumps, goes right back and gently turns it into the legside
Zampa to Root, 2 runs tossed up, a bit too full, allows Root to sweep to deep square leg

Zampa to Root, OUT caught at slip. The move works, both to bring in Zampa and to have a slip for the right-hander. Nicely tossed up, Root's taking a step forward, but the ball dips before he can get to the pitch and turns just enough to take the outside edge. Smart take from Finch, to his right.
Zampa to Buttler, no run tossed up, full on the stumps, driven to a very straight mid-on
Zampa to Buttler, 1 run some drift into him but a bit too full, shovelled to fine leg
Zampa to Morgan, no run length ball on the stumps, stays still and carefully pats it down towards short leg
Marsh to Buttler, 1 run back of a length on off, turned backward of square
Marsh to Morgan, no run fuller outside off, driven but off the toe-end and cover fields
Marsh to Morgan, 1 run dug in short but doesn't bounce much, Morgan pulls to deep square leg.
Marsh to Buttler, 1 run half a step down the track and flicks this length ball from his pads to fine leg
Marsh to Morgan, FOUR runs gorgeous. Full outside off, comes on the front foot and uses his wrists to power a drive over cover and into the boundary
Marsh to Morgan, 1 run length on off, pushes it gently but wide of the fielder at cover and towards long-off for a single
Zampa to Morgan, no run fuller on off, driven to mid-off
Zampa to Morgan, FOUR runs reverse swept fine and he'll get a boundary. Great execution. Tossed up on off and he committed to the shot early, and got the placement right

Zampa to Morgan, FOUR runs oh nicely done. Morgan's shifted gears from 2 to 5 in the blink of an eye almost. Not that tossed up, but he gets to the pitch with a stride and uses wrists to drive over the in-field
Zampa to Morgan, no run flatter and quicker, nudged to short third man
Zampa to Morgan, no run length on the stumps, pushed back to the bowler
Zampa to Morgan, no run slightly quicker, played into the offside on the back foot
Cummins to Buttler, no run length in the channel, moving away, pushes at it but beaten
Cummins to Buttler, no run fuller on off, clipped to midwicket

Cummins to Buttler, OUT trapped in front but Buttler reviews immediately. Inside edge? After moving the last one away, Cummins brought this one back in. Buttler was pushing at it and it beats his bat. No inside edge. Hits in line and umpire's call on hitting the stumps! Buttler will have to go, what a great bowling change once again from Finch.
Cummins to Billings, no run length ball coming into him, defended towards mid-on
Cummins to Billings, no run length on off, angling into him from a bit wider of the crease, steered to backward point
Cummins to Billings, no run yorker on off stump, dug out to mid-on. No single. wicket maiden
Zampa to Morgan, 1 run length outside off, opens the face to guide to point
Zampa to Billings, no run nice drift, on a length, pushes him back and he tentatively jabs it down
Zampa to Billings, 1 run tossed up outside off, fuller, slaps a drive to extra cover
Zampa to Morgan, no run tossed up outside off, clipped back to the bowler on the front foot
Zampa to Morgan, 1 run tossed up on leg stump, turned to short fine leg's right
Zampa to Billings, no run tossed up full on the stumps, whips a drive, but to mid-on
Cummins to Morgan, no run length ball coming into him, punched back

Cummins to Morgan, FOUR runs stunning from Morgan. Seemed like an off-balance push but it goes straight past the bowler and into the boundary. He was making room, Cummins bowled it full, Morgan seemed to gently punch it back, off the toe end of the bat. Timed well enough to go all the way
Cummins to Morgan, 1 run short outside off, pulls with authority but Marnus is at deep square leg and fields
Cummins to Billings, no run beaten. Length ball outside off, Billings is getting down low to steer it but it bounces over his bat
Cummins to Billings, 1 run banged in short, rises up to the helmet but Billings takes it on, swivels back and pulls to deep square leg
Cummins to Morgan, no run length on the stumps, punched to midwicket
Zampa to Billings, no run gets some drift, fuller on le gstump, turned to short fine leg

Zampa to Billings, no run down the track and pushes to mid-on. Wants a single but is wisely sent back. Mid-on and mid-off are both in the circle. and almost carelessly run out was Billings but he's back in the crease. The throw came in and Carey whipped off the bails. Billings was ambling back with bat stuck outside the crease but stepped inside with boot in time
Zampa to Billings, no run pushed to mid-on
Zampa to Billings, 1 run fuller and swept hard, deep square leg cleans up

Zampa to Morgan, OUT huge shout not given and Finch reviews. Great loop on this, pitches on a length on middle and turns past his forward defensive to hit him on the knee roll. and it's three reds so that's a fabulous review and an extremely critical wicket. Excellent bowling. Drew him forward, got the ball to dip and turn enough to beat bat but not enough to be missing the stumps
Zampa to Woakes, no run fullish on off, comes forward and jams his bat in defence
Cummins to Billings, no run length on the stumps, defended back to the bowler
Cummins to Billings, no run fuller on the stumps, full face of the bat in defence, bounces over the leaping bowler
Cummins to Billings, no run kept low, but Billings did well to get his bat down in time and defend into the offside. Length outside off and jagging back into him
Cummins to Billings, no run tight line and length nibbling around off stump steered to point
Cummins to Billings, no run length on the fourth stump again, guided to backward point.
Cummins to Billings, no run fuller on the stumps, punched nicely but straight to mid-on. Another maiden
Zampa to Woakes, no run googly, stretches well forward to defend towards mid-on
Zampa to Woakes, no run length ball on off, pushed with the turn to cover
Zampa to Woakes, no run huge shout but not given again. Inside edge on that. No review. Googly, quicker one that he didn't pick, and was caught on the crease.
Zampa to Woakes, no run
Zampa to Woakes, no run tossed up on the stumps, driven to short cover

Zampa to Woakes, 1 run length ball on the stumps pushed gently and Zampa a bit sloppy there, could have got a maiden for himself and two in a row for Australia by moving to his left and fielding but slips up. They get a single
Hazlewood to Woakes, no run full, tailing into him, driven to mid-off
Hazlewood to Woakes, no run beaten. Backing away, but this is on off, on back of a length and moving in a touch. He can't get bat on it
Hazlewood to Woakes, no run fuller on the pads, flicked away but short midwicket dives to his left to field
Hazlewood to Woakes, FOUR runs flayed through cover and that will break the shackles a bit. Fuller on off, comes on the front foot and slams it
Hazlewood to Woakes, no run another one keeps low. Length around off and nipping in, Billings gets his bat down in time to keep the ball out
Hazlewood to Woakes, no run length ball nipping in, goes to drive, gets it off the inside half of the bat to mid-on.
Zampa to Billings, 1 run tossed up on off, driven inside out past extra cover
Zampa to Woakes, no run sharply spinning googly, pitches well outside off and cuts back in. He didn't read it but had enough time to jab it away
Zampa to Woakes, no run fuller, clipped to mid-on
Zampa to Woakes, FOUR runs full toss, and he doesn't let the gift go. Flat bats it straight past the bowler, good timing and gets the boundary
Zampa to Woakes, no run length on off, steered to point
Zampa to Woakes, no run tossed up full on the stumps, driven to mid-off
Hazlewood to Billings, no run moves well across his stumps to a full ball outside off but can only defend it into the offside
Hazlewood to Billings, no run keeping a tight line outside off, defended towards gully
Hazlewood to Billings, no run back of a length and nipping in, Billings goes to pull but is struck on the thigh pad
Hazlewood to Billings, 1 run length ball on off, walks across and works it through square
Hazlewood to Woakes, no run fuller on off, goes to drive, gets it off the inside half of the bat as it trickles to mid-on
Hazlewood to Woakes, 1 run good connection with the pull shot. Short ball outside off and he hits it sweetly but there is a sweeper who'll clean up
Zampa to Woakes, FOUR runs tossed up on leg stump, but that is a super shot by Woakes. Too full and flicks it with the spin - was the googly - and places it between mid-on and midwicket
Zampa to Woakes, no run good length on the stumps, comes on the front foot to defend
Zampa to Woakes, 1 run tossed up on off, driven to long-off
Zampa to Billings, 1 run flatter on middle and leg, swept to deep square leg
Zampa to Woakes, no run quicker and a bit shorter, on leg and turning across, whipped to midwicket
Zampa to Woakes, no run tossed up, dips and spins past his bat as he's coming on the front foot to push
Starc to Billings, no run full one angling into him, driven to extra cover
Starc to Billings, 1 run length ball into him on the stumps, steered to point's right from close to his body, with bat close to pad
Starc to Woakes, no run length outside off, comes on the front foot and reaches to drive. Fielded by cover
Starc to Woakes, 2 runs full into his pads, flicked uppishly but clears midwicket
Starc to Woakes, 1 run fuller outside off, driven to deep cover
Starc to Billings, 1 run full on the stumps, driven to mid-on

Zampa to Billings, OUT chopped on! Billings gave himself room to cut but this was too straight and cramped him for room. A flat legbreak, just a hint of turn and it zipped through, taking the bottom edge and diverted onto the stumps. Slightly fuller than Billings anticipated
Zampa to Sam Curran, 1 run googly, fenced to point where Starc misfields, and Curran gets off the mark straightaway
Zampa to Woakes, 1 run tossed up on off stump, Woakes presses out to long-off
Zampa to Sam Curran, no run nudged into the covers defensively
Zampa to Sam Curran, no run googly again, blocked out to cover
Zampa to Sam Curran, no run legbreak, shovelled into the leg side off the hip
Starc to Woakes, no run length outside off, inside-edged towards mid-on
Starc to Woakes, no run wide on the crease, Woakes digs out a full ball, nudging towards cover
Starc to Woakes, no run fullish on fifth stump, driven into the covers but Warner gets down brilliantly from in tight to stop it getting through the ring
Starc to Woakes, no run banged in on a length at 89mph/144kph, Woakes looks to work to leg but only manages to squirt into the covers via a leading edge
Starc to Woakes, 1 run low full toss, driven out to deep cover. Attempted yorker, slightly overpitched

Starc to Sam Curran, OUT nicks him off! Or does he? Gough, standing in his first game since the third Test vs Pakistan, isn't sure if it carried through to Carey. Starc ran his fingers down the side of this, hitting a length on fifth stump, and drew an outside edge as Curran looked to steer towards third man. The catch is a tight call, but it looks like it's going to be given, as Carey had just about got his gloves under the ball. Curran
Hazlewood to Woakes, 1 run bit of late movement back in as Woakes inside-edges into the back pad. Strangled appeal, but definitely bat first
Hazlewood to Tom Curran, no run length ball angling in towards the top of off at 88mph/141kph, defended towards mid-on
Hazlewood to Tom Curran, no run length on sixth stump, steered to backward point
Hazlewood to Tom Curran, no run searing yorker at 87mph/141kph, dug out into the leg side
Hazlewood to Tom Curran, no run back of a length, Curran defends while jumping onto the back foot
Hazlewood to Tom Curran, no run length on fifth stump, pressed out to mid-off
Starc to Woakes, no run wide on the crease, Woakes gives himself some room but only defends into the covers

Starc to Woakes, FOUR runs half-volley, wide outside off, and Woakes frees his arms, lofting over short cover and flaying this away for four! Room to extend the arms, and gets it comfortably over the man in tight
Starc to Woakes, 1 run length ball, tucked off the hip out to square leg
Starc to Tom Curran, no run full on leg stump, Curran misses out as he nudges defensively towards mid-on. Hint of late tail on that - ball seems to be reversing
Starc to Tom Curran, no run attempted slower ball, turns into a low full toss on fifth stump but Curran only pats back down the pitch

Marsh to Tom Curran, FOUR runs uses his feet again, freeing his arms to a straight length ball and hacking it over midwicket for four! Heaved over the ring, and races away after a couple of bounces

Zampa to Tom Curran, no run lebgreak, down the leg side, and tucked round the corner to short fine leg

Starc to Tom Curran, FOUR runs attempted yorker, which turns into a low full toss. Curran digs it out with an angled bat, opening the face and running it away through third man. Hint of edge, and it runs away fine for four!

Starc to Tom Curran, FOUR runs length ball, Curran looks to go down the ground and crunches it back over Starc's head for four more! Stood pretty still, cleared the front leg, and heaved it for four

Starc to Tom Curran, no run full outside off, and late tail away from the bat takes it past Curran's swing
Starc to Tom Curran, 1 run fullish on fourth stump, driven out into the off side for a single

Cummins to Rashid, FOUR runs full outside off, Rashid frees the arms and lofts over backward point for four to bring up the 50 partnership! Cleared the front leg, opened the face, and chipped it behind square
Cummins to Rashid, no run Rashid swats awkwardly at a short ball, which beats him and flies through to Carey

Cummins to Rashid, SIX runs banged in, back of a length, and Rashid swats at it, sending it over the rope for six! Didn't quite get up as he'd have liked, and Rashid cleared the front leg, hooking towards the shorter boundary. The wind carried it over Labuschagne on the rope, and it's half a dozen more!
Cummins to Rashid, FOUR runs length outside off, Rashid slugs in front of square and picks up four more! Looked like a slower ball, and Rashid shifted his weight forward, heaving through midwicket

Marsh to Tom Curran, OUT cleaned up this time! A vital 76-run partnership finally comes to an end. Pace on this time, slightly full of a length, and it crashes into middle and leg as Curran looks to heave over the leg side
Marsh to Archer, 2 runs length on fifth stump, slashed out to wide long-off and they race back for two

Marsh to Archer, FOUR runs slower ball into the pitch, Archer swings cross-batted and sends it back over Marsh's head for four! He set himself early, anticipating the short ball, and picked the slower ball early, bludgeoning it dead-straight down the ground

4.54pm: So England end on 231 for 9, and I doubt Australia will find it easy to knock those off and seal the series. Batting was a real struggle for England on a tough pitch, with Starc and Hazlewood irresistible with the new ball and Zampa superb through the middle. But Tom Curran added 76 in 9.3 overs with Rashid to propel England to a competitive score, and with a couple of early breakthroughs, they will be right in this one. Saurabh will be
Woakes to Warner, 1 run full on middle and leg, clipped to square leg. Sloppy work from England first up, allowing the single, with Tom Curran failing to collect the ball cleanly
Woakes to Finch, no run length on the stumps, moving a touch away, Finch hops into the tuck past short midwicket, but can't go past mid-on

Woakes to Finch, 1 run full on the stumps, driven back firmly and he sets off for the single. Woakes got his hand to it and half-stopped it. Mid-off swoops in and lets fly a throw. Finch wasn't even in the frame but the ball doesn't hit the stumps. Morgan the fielder

Rashid to Finch, no run tosses up a sharply-spun legbreak, which turns sharply away from the bat as Finch looks to heave another boundary over long-on
Archer to Labuschagne, 1 leg bye cross-seamer which nips away from Labuschagne as he looks to work to leg. He yelps in pain as he is struck on the back thigh pad, and Archer lets out a wry smile
Archer to Finch, no run length ball on fourth stump at 85mph/137kph, which Finch bravely leaves alone. It zips just past the top of off, vindicating his decision
Archer to Finch, no run banged in, slightly full of a length at 86mph/138kph. Finch inside-edges into the leg side, looking to play a checked drive
Archer to Finch, 2 runs full and straight, tucked off the pads behind square for a couple as Billings gives chase.
Archer to Finch, no run yorker on off stump at 87mph/141kph, dug out towards mid-on. Finch is stung by some vibrations as that thuds into the toe
Archer to Finch, no run fullish on fourth stump, Finch pushes back towards Archer's left hand
Woakes to Labuschagne, no run length on fifth stump, keeps a little low as Labuschagne jams the bat down to defend
Woakes to Labuschagne, 1 run length ball on sixth stump, guided down to third man with an open face
Woakes to Finch, no run length ball on fifth stump, angling in and nipping away to beat Finch's outside edge, as he prods awkwardly at this away from his body
Woakes to Finch, no run length ball on the stumps, clipped to wide mid-on

Woakes to Finch, 2 runs length on fourth stump, tip-and-run into the off side for a single that is never there, but Roy's throw is wide! Never a single, but Roy's throw to the keeper's end was wayward from backward point, and they steal a second run as Bairstow falls over while backing up. Chaos!
Woakes to Finch, no run nudged defensively into the leg side
Archer to Labuschagne, 1 run slower ball on a length, steered to backward point for a sharp single. Looked like a legcutter, I think
Archer to Finch, no run short ball in at the ribs, 89mph/143kph, and Finch wears one as he is late on the pull. Smashed him between the left pectoral and the biceps, and Finch swears in pain
Archer to Finch, no run length on sixth stump, Finch jumps onto the back foot to punch it straight to short cover
Archer to Finch, 1 run slightly back of a length, and Finch swats it down to long leg to retain the strike
Woakes to Finch, no run beauty on a length in the channel which beats Finch! Fifth stump, on a length, and Finch dangles his bat at it optimistically
Woakes to Finch, no run in the slot on the stumps, pushed uppishly towards mid-off on the bounce
Woakes to Finch, 1 run slightly full of a length on fourth stump, nudged into the covers for a quick single

Woakes to Labuschagne, FOUR runs Labuschagne shimmies over to the off side and takes a step down the pitch. Woakes drags his length back, but it sits up nicely for him and he pulls sweetly through backward square for four!
Woakes to Labuschagne, 1 run nudged out to square leg for one, which brings up the 100-run stand from only 128 balls. These two have put Australia in control
Woakes to Finch, no run wide on the crease, bold leave from Finch as this keeps slightly low and nearly brushes his off stump! Nearly made to look very silly

Archer to Labuschagne, 1 run short outside off at 87mph/141kph. Labuschagne shapes to leave, but dangles the bat in the way of the ball to steer it down to third man for one. Not sure he knew much about where that was going
Archer to Finch, 1 run tight to the stumps, Archer hits a length at 88mph/141kph, and Finch pushes effortlessly to deep cover
Archer to Labuschagne, no run slower ball, full on the stumps, and dug out towards mid-on. Might have been the knuckleball, dipped in late

Archer to Labuschagne, 2 runs back of a length, steered through gully and down to third man for a sharp two. Rashid should probably have done better running in from the boundary, but great running from Australia yet again

Archer to Labuschagne, 1 run length in the channel at 89mph/144kph, Labuschagne is late on it, and steers an awkward upper-cut over gully as he looks to withdraw the bat. Gets lucky, and it loops up to Rashid on the bounce
Archer to Finch, 1 run full and straight, tickled down to fine leg to keep the strike
Woakes to Finch, no run straight length ball, Finch defends back down the pitch, jumping onto the back foot
Woakes to Finch, no run banged in on a length, cut out to point on the bounce where Roy fields
Woakes to Finch, no run length on off stump, nudged to short extra cover
Woakes to Finch, 1 run length outside off, pressed out to cover and they scamper through for another tight single

Woakes to Labuschagne, OUT trapped on the pad, Woakes lets out a desperate appeal but Gough says no. Morgan reviews immediately. This struck both pads as he looked to work a length ball to leg, but crucially hit the front one first. No bat, Ultra-Edge confirms. Hits him in line, and would have smashed into middle two-thirds of the way up! Marnus has to trudge off, and Woakes has the breakthrough
Woakes to Marsh, 1 run length outside off, pressed out into the covers
Archer to Marsh, no run back of a length at 87mph/140kph, Marsh rides the bounce to guide into the covers
Archer to Marsh, no run banged in on a length at 87mph/140kph, and steered towards cover-point
Archer to Marsh, no run back of a length, Marsh rides the bounce and pushes into the covers
Archer to Marsh, no run slower ball on a length, steered straight to point with an open face
Archer to Carey, no run short ball in at the hip, Carey prods awkwardly at it and thinks about one but is sent back by Finch
Woakes to Finch, no run length ball nipping in, defended from the crease
Woakes to Finch, no run fuller outside off, goes to drive it, toe-ends it to short cover
Woakes to Maxwell, no run ooh went a long way across, but got his bat in front of his pad and nudged it to midwicket
Woakes to Maxwell, no run length on off, keeps a bit low, jams his bat down
Woakes to Maxwell, 1 run comes on the front foot and opens the face to steer to third man

Archer to Maxwell, no run short fast, and into his rib cage. Maxwell wasn't even looking at it just turned around into a half-hearted pull. The ball thuds into bat. It was ball hitting bat, not bat hitting ball. 91 mph
Archer to Maxwell, no run length on off, defended on the front foot
Archer to Maxwell, no run slower one, at just 77 mph, nipping into him. Just about defended by Maxwell
Archer to Maxwell, 1 leg bye tailing into him at 89 mph, flicks the pad and goes to short fine leg. Lots of leg-byes off Archer today
Archer to Carey, no run full, almost yorker length but solid in defence is Carey

Archer to Carey, no run and Archer ends a fantastic day with the ball with a sharply jagging in delivery that hits Carey on the thigh pad, defeating his back foot defence. Half an appeal but that was too high.
Woakes to Cummins, 1 run full and angling into him, straightens a bit, Cummins forward defence is more hopeful than convincing, squirts off the edge to third man
Woakes to Carey, 1 run pushed into the offside on the front foot
Woakes to Cummins, no run full and on off, defended to cover

Woakes to Cummins, no run edge doesn't carry to slip. Pushing down the wrong line again, the ball also straightened off a length on middle. But soft hands so the ball bounces well before reaching Root at slip
Woakes to Cummins, 1 run goes for the yorker, but ends up as a low full toss on the stumps, turned away to square leg
Rashid to Cummins, 1 run googly that he didn't read, was coming forward to defend, takes the inside edge and rolls backward of square
Rashid to Carey, 1 run too full, and he comes on the front foot to flick this to wide long-on
Rashid to Cummins, no run tossed up, ends as a full toss, but Cummins can't put it away. Patted tamely to mid-on
Rashid to Cummins, no run big-spinning leg-break and Cummins was targetting cow corner with a big slog-sweep. Defeated completely
Rashid to Cummins, 1 run plays it more carefully this time, coming forward to a tossed up delivery and gently steering towards point
Rashid to Carey, 2 runs nicely done, saw the ball full and swept it fine. The man at fine leg is square so has to run to his left to field
Tom Curran to Cummins, 1 leg bye back of a length on leg stump, takes the pads to roll towards leg gully
Tom Curran to Carey, no run length into him to tuck him up, patted towards short midwicket
Tom Curran to Carey, no run hisses past the outside edge as Carey is caught on the crease and poking at it. Keeps bat close to body though
Tom Curran to Carey, no run back of a length angling in on off, tapped towards mid-on
Tom Curran to Carey, no run rapped on the pads but that's going down. Angling into him, and he can't connect with the flick off his pads
Tom Curran to Carey, no run length ball outside off, and pushed to mid-off
Rashid to Cummins, no run tossed up outside off, gets him to stretch forward and pat it in defence
Rashid to Cummins, no run teasing loop, dips and grips to turn past the hopeful forward defensive prod
Rashid to Cummins, SIX runs boom. Rashid goes too full and Cummins gets a free swing of his arms to loft this over long-on. Way over.
Rashid to Cummins, no run length outside off, defended
Rashid to Cummins, no run big spin again, pitched short of a length and spun across him, he stayed in his crease and followed the ball with his hands to defend
Rashid to Cummins, no run beaten again, big stride out to defend but the ball spins past the bat
Tom Curran to Carey, no run length outside off, defended to cover on the front foot
Tom Curran to Carey, 1 run length outside off, tapped through cover
Tom Curran to Cummins, 1 run squirted away through backward point
Tom Curran to Carey, 1 run length outside off, opens the face to run it down to third man
Tom Curran to Cummins, no run bounces a bit more than Cummins expects it to and he gets it high on the bat as it pops up. No short leg though and it lands there
Tom Curran to Cummins, no run length outside off, punched to mid-off
Sam Curran to Carey, 1 run back of a length outside off, cuts it to deep point. Good work by the fielder to run to his left and keep them to one run
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run full on the stumps and Zampa offers the full face of the bat to defend and keep out the hat-trick ball
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run fuller into him, defended to mid-off
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run full and outside off again, defended into the offside again
Tom Curran to Carey, 1 leg bye length ball angling into him, tries to play it with the angle, the ball trickles towards short fine leg
Tom Curran to Zampa, no run length outside off, pushes it back to the bowler's left
Tom Curran to Zampa, 1 run angling into him straighter and he manages to nurdle it to fine leg. Tom Curran holds his head in his hands, he didn't want to give away that single. Wanted Zampa on strike
Tom Curran to Carey, 1 run fuller on the leg stump, flicked off his toes through midwicket
Tom Curran to Zampa, no run back of a length outside off, no pace or bounce to work with, his push finds the toe-end of the bat hitting ball and it not travelling very far
Tom Curran to Zampa, no run fuller on off, pushed firmly to mid-off

Sam Curran to Carey, 3 runs short and wide outside off, cuts it nicely through backward point. Good effort in the deep by Tom Currant to run around and cut off the boundary but the attempted relay through goes awry as he lobs it out of Morgan's reach. That allows the batsmen to take a third
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run hit on a hard length from wide of the crease around the wicket and straightening a touch, solid defence offered
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run full on off, driven on the front foot, but short cover intercepts
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run length ball nibbling in the off stump area, punches into cover
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run zips in on off stump again, and he offers a straight bat in defence
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run nice change-up, bouncer to end the over that passes over off stump, Zampa is not expecting that, tries to upper cut it but is too late on it
Tom Curran to Carey, no run fuller on off, punched to point
Tom Curran to Carey, 1 run angling into him a bit fuller, clipped to mid-on
Tom Curran to Zampa, no run swing and a miss. back of a length on the off stump and angling in, he clears his front leg to swipe across the line. Doesn't connect. The ball goes over the stumps
Tom Curran to Zampa, 1 run back of a length again, this time he goes back in his crease and punches it straight, gets it past the bowler
Tom Curran to Carey, 1 run fuller and a bit too straight, clipped to mid-on's right
Tom Curran to Zampa, no run was backing away but Tom saw that and followed him, ends up inside-edging a drive towards square leg
Sam Curran to Carey, 1 run length on off, tight line, bunted to mid-on
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run stepping away to make room again, but Same also follows him and he's gone so far down leg that the ball beats his outside edge while going past leg-stump line
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run and he changes up from bowling it short and into him to bowling a yorker on the fifth stump. Zampa tries to get low and get bat on it but can't. Good, smart bowling
Sam Curran to Zampa, no run length ball outside off, another big swipe across the line, takes the bottom edge off the end of the bat and bounces down
Sam Curran to Carey, 1 run inside edge onto pad off his attempted punch, but he ball goes slowly into the covers and they take a single
Tom Curran to Carey, 1 run backs away but Curran follows him and he can only mis-time the pull to wide long-on. Doesn't get a second
Tom Curran to Hazlewood, 1 run length ball angling into him on the pads, comfortably tucked through square leg for a single
Tom Curran to Carey, no run saw him backing away and he bowls a slower ball full and wide of off. Carey ends up trying to reach for it and can't connect
Tom Curran to Carey, no run punchy drive but straight to extra cover. This was full and on middle, he made some room and connected well, but not in the gap
Tom Curran to Carey, 1 run back of a length, swats a pull to wide long-on, again not well timed
Tom Curran to Hazlewood, 1 run oh he's going to take the single and keep strike. Fuller on the pads, glanced to fine leg
Sam Curran to Hazlewood, no run floats up a fuller ball on the stumps, flicked to short midwicket

Sam Curran to Hazlewood, 1 leg bye slips in the short ball, Hazlewood tries o paddle-pull it and the ball misses bat but hits his body and drops at his feet. Sam rushes across in his follow through and kicks the ball onto the stumps but Carey was quick off the blocks and makes his ground
Sam Curran to Carey, 1 run just can't get them away. This one is dug into a length and doesn't come on to the bat as Carey shapes to slap it away. Gets it through cover but no further
Sam Curran to Hazlewood, 1 run length on off, patted to long-on
Sam Curran to Carey, no run tries to drive, but no timing, and straight back down the pitch
Sam Curran to Carey, 1 run keeps the strike for the next over with a single through square leg
Rashid to Carey, 1 run googly, pulled across the line out to deep backward square
Rashid to Hazlewood, 1 run googly again, Hazlewood keeps his eye on it and pulls unconvincingly for one through midwicket

Rashid to Carey, 2 runs brings out the reverse, jumping across towards the leg side, and laps it to Tom Curran at third man who put it down! Leaping at full stretch, gets a fingertip on it, and parries it down to third man
Rashid to Carey, 1 run fired into the pitch, heaved out to long-on for one more
Rashid to Hazlewood, 1 run flat legbreak, clipped off the hip for one more to square leg

Rashid to Carey, FOUR runs brings out the slog-sweep to a full ball, flat on off stump, and finally gets his first boundary! Eventually gets one out the middle, and it races away in front of square to beat Billings diving to his right at deep midwicket
Sam Curran to Hazlewood, 1 run bustling medium pace, tight to the stumps, and Hazlewood clips into the leg side from the top of off to get off strike
Sam Curran to Carey, 1 run banged in on a length, punched out towards wide extra cover and they pinch a single
Sam Curran to Hazlewood, 1 run width outside the off stump, cut away in front of square to get Carey back on strike

Sam Curran to Carey, FOUR runs back of a length, Carey gets it up over mid-off for four! Slightly too short from Curran, banged into the pitch, and Carey swung hard, cross-batted, to send it over the rope after a couple of bounces
Sam Curran to Carey, 2 runs bustling line and length, Carey heaves it down the ground with a grunt, but no timing. It trickles down towards long-on, and they'll pinch a second run
Sam Curran to Carey, 1 run back of a length, tucked out to square leg to keep the strike
Rashid to Carey, 1 run flat and fullish, goes for the slog-sweep, but only gets the bottom edge to short fine leg.
Rashid to Hazlewood, 1 leg bye quick single taken. Tossed up googly that Hazlewood didn't read, was trying to tickle it fine, goes into the offside
Rashid to Carey, no run googly and he misses it! Clearing his front leg to sweep that into oblivion, can't get bat on it with the google floated up on off and turning away
England won by 24 runs
Player of the match is Jofra Archer, ENG
